
[1]nereid

   NEREID, n. In mythology, a sea nymph. In ancient monuments, the Nereids
   are represented as riding on sea horses, sometimes with the human form
   entire, and sometimes with the tail of a fish. They were the daughters
   of Nereus, and constantly attended Neptune.
